#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-path` and `quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-domain` properties control which application paths the state and session cookies will be available at. The wider the cookie-path is (\"/\"), the wider the application secured space can be. You may want to restrict it to more specific paths such as `/secured`, to make it easier to handle the public space available at paths such as `/public`.\n"
"You may also want to restrict it when the specific endpoint paths should only be accessible by users who authenticated with specific providers only. For example, `/keycloak` path can only accessible by users authenticated with Keycloak, `/google` - with Google, etc. See also the <<multi-tenancy>> section for more information."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-path` 和 `quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-domain` 属性用于控制状态 Cookie 和会话 Cookie 将在哪些应用程序路径上可用。cookie-path 的范围越广（“/”），应用程序受保护的范围就越广。 您可能希望将其限制为更具体的路径（例如 `/secured` ），以便更轻松地处理 `/public` 等路径上的公共区域。 此外，当特定端点路径仅应允许通过特定提供商进行身份验证的用户访问时，您可能也需要进行限制。例如， `/keycloak` 路径仅允许通过 Keycloak 进行身份验证的用户访问， `/google` 路径仅允许通过 Google 进行身份验证的用户访问，以此类推。有关更多信息，请参阅“ <<multi-tenancy>> ”部分。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-path-header` can be used to dynamically set the required cookie path - this property should be used with care and only when it fits your deployment requirements."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-path-header` 可用于动态设置所需的 Cookie 路径——使用此属性时应谨慎，且仅在符合您的部署要求时才应使用。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-same-site` defines a `Same-Site` attribute for a session cookie as `lax` by default, since setting it to `strict` proved to be breaking some deployments. However, setting it to `strict` is RECOMMENDED when it is known to work in your deployment, for example, when the OIDC provider is hosted in the same domain as the application, etc."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-same-site` 默认将会话 Cookie 的 `Same-Site` 属性设置为 `“lax` ”，因为将该属性设置为 `“strict` ”已被证实会导致某些部署出现问题。 不过，如果已确认该设置在您的部署环境中能够正常工作（例如，当 OIDC 提供商与应用程序托管在同一域名下时），则建议将其设置为 `“strict”` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Similarly, `quarkus.oidc.authentication.state-cookie-same-site` defines a `Same-Site` attribute for a state cookie as `lax` by default, but setting it to `strict` is RECOMMENDED when it is known to work in your deployment."
msgstr "同样 `，quarkus.oidc.authentication.state-cookie-same-site` 默认将状态 Cookie 的 `Same-Site` 属性定义为 `“lax` ”，但在已确认该设置在您的部署环境中可正常工作的情况下，建议将其设置为 `“strict”` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ideally both the session and state cookies have the same `Same-Site` attribute value, however having the same `Same-Site` `strict` value for both cookies also proved to be problematic in some cases."
msgstr "理想情况下，会话 Cookie 和状态 Cookie 的 `Same-Site` 属性值应相同；然而，在某些情况下，将这两个 Cookie 的 `Same-Site` 属性值都 `设为“strict”` 也会引发问题。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-suffix` can be used to customize the state and session cookie names. For example, by setting `%test.quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-suffix=test` you can have the session cookie name qualified with the `_test` suffix in the test profile only."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-suffix` 可用于自定义状态和会话 Cookie 的名称。例如，通过设置 `%test.quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-suffix=test，` 您可以仅在测试配置文件中，使会话 Cookie 的名称带有 `_test` 后缀。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/security-oidc-expanded-configuration.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-force-secure` may only be relevant in some deployments if Quarkus is listening on non-secure HTTP protocol but running behind HTTPS terminating reverse proxy. This property has no impact if Quarkus is listening on HTTPS, when cookies are always secure."
msgstr "`quarkus.oidc.authentication.cookie-force-secure` 仅在某些部署场景下才可能相关，即当 Quarkus 监听非安全 HTTP 协议，但运行在 HTTPS 终止反向代理之后时。如果 Quarkus 监听的是 HTTPS，则该属性不会产生影响，因为此时 Cookie 始终是安全的。"

